<!-- Overview -->
<section id="overview">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>VB includes a print optimization layer that automatically makes pages look good when printed. It resets design tokens for black-on-white contrast, hides interactive elements, controls page breaks, expands external links, and linearizes layouts.</p>

  <p>The print layer loads automatically via <code>main.css</code>. No extra imports needed.</p>

  <p>For most pages, the default behavior is all you need. For pages that are <em>intended</em> to be printed (articles, invoices, reports), use <code>data-print</code> on the <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> to enable enhanced print modes with <code>@page</code> rules.</p>

  <p>For a conceptual overview, see the <a href="/docs/printing/">Printing guide</a>.</p>
</section>


<!-- Page Modes -->
<section id="page-modes">
  <h2>Page Modes</h2>
  <p>Set <code>data-print</code> on <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> to activate a named print mode. Each mode maps to a CSS <code>@page</code> rule with optimized margins and page numbering.</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Value</th>
        <th>Effect</th>
        <th>Use Case</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>article</code></td>
        <td>Wide margins, page numbers (bottom center), no number on first page, section breaks</td>
        <td>Blog posts, documentation, long-form content</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>invoice</code></td>
        <td>Tight margins, A4 portrait</td>
        <td>Invoices, receipts, order confirmations</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>report</code></td>
        <td>Left/right page awareness, binding margin, page numbers in outer corners</td>
        <td>Multi-page reports, booklets</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>none</code></td>
        <td>Hides the entire page from printing</td>
        <td>Dashboards, app shells, settings pages</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  {% set _codeMode %}<!-- Long-form article -->
<body data-print="article">

<!-- Invoice -->
<body data-print="invoice">

<!-- Multi-page report -->
<body data-print="report">

<!-- Never print this page -->
<body data-print="none">

<!-- Default: basic print cleanup, no @page enhancements -->
<body>{% endset %}
  <code-block language="html" label="Page mode examples">{{ _codeMode | escape }}</code-block>

  <p>In <code>article</code> mode, each direct <code>&lt;section&gt;</code> child of <code>[data-print="article"]</code> starts on a new page.</p>
</section>


<!-- Visibility -->
<section id="visibility">
  <h2>Visibility Attributes</h2>
  <p>Control what appears on screen vs. paper.</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Attribute</th>
        <th>Effect</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-no-print</code></td>
        <td>Hidden when printed, visible on screen</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-screen-only</code></td>
        <td>Alias for <code>data-no-print</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-print-only</code></td>
        <td>Visible when printed, hidden on screen</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-print-keep</code></td>
        <td>Prevents auto-hiding of <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;aside&gt;</code> that would normally be suppressed</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-print-background</code></td>
        <td>Forces background colors/images to print (uses <code>print-color-adjust: exact</code>)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  {% set _codeVis %}<!-- Only visible when printed -->
<p data-print-only>Printed from example.com on Feb 24, 2026.</p>

<!-- Hidden when printed -->
<footer data-no-print>
  <p>&copy; 2026 Example Site</p>
</footer>

<!-- Keep this nav in print (normally nav is hidden) -->
<nav aria-label="Table of contents" data-print-keep>
  <ol>
    <li><a href="#intro">Introduction</a></li>
    <li><a href="#methods">Methods</a></li>
  </ol>
</nav>

<!-- Force background color to print -->
<mark data-print-background>Highlighted text</mark>{% endset %}
  <code-block language="html" label="Visibility control">{{ _codeVis | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>What Gets Auto-Hidden</h3>
  <p>These elements are hidden in print automatically (no attributes needed):</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>&lt;nav&gt;</code> (unless <code>data-print-keep</code> is set)</li>
    <li><code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;search&gt;</code></li>
    <li>Buttons (except <code>type="submit"</code>)</li>
    <li>Range inputs, switches, toolbars</li>
    <li>VB interactive components: <code>theme-picker</code>, <code>site-search</code>, <code>command-palette</code>, <code>page-toc</code>, <code>tool-tip</code>, <code>toast-msg</code>, <code>short-cuts</code>, <code>settings-panel</code>, <code>drop-down</code>, <code>context-menu</code>, <code>emoji-picker</code>, <code>print-page</code></li>
  </ul>
</section>


<!-- Page Breaks -->
<section id="page-breaks">
  <h2>Page Break Control</h2>
  <p>Force or prevent page breaks on specific elements.</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Attribute</th>
        <th>CSS Effect</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-break-before</code></td>
        <td><code>break-before: page</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-break-after</code></td>
        <td><code>break-after: page</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-break-avoid</code></td>
        <td><code>break-inside: avoid</code></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  {% set _codeBreak %}<!-- Start this section on a new page -->
<section data-break-before>
  <h2>Chapter 2: Methods</h2>
  ...
</section>

<!-- Keep this figure from splitting across pages -->
<figure data-break-avoid>
  <img src="chart.svg" alt="Results chart">
  <figcaption>Figure 1: Quarterly results</figcaption>
</figure>{% endset %}
  <code-block language="html" label="Page break examples">{{ _codeBreak | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3>Automatic Break Protection</h3>
  <p>VB automatically prevents breaks inside these elements (no attribute needed):</p>
  <p><code>table</code>, <code>blockquote</code>, <code>pre</code>, <code>code</code>, <code>figure</code>, <code>li</code>, <code>img</code>, <code>picture</code>, <code>details</code>, <code>fieldset</code></p>
  <p>Headings are kept with their following paragraph &mdash; a heading will never appear alone at the bottom of a page.</p>
</section>


<!-- Print Component -->
<section id="print-component">
  <h2>Print Component</h2>
  <p>The <code>&lt;print-page&gt;</code> web component provides a print button that auto-hides itself when printing.</p>

  {% set _codePrint %}<print-page>Print this page</print-page>

<!-- With raw-mode toggle (lets users disable VB print styles) -->
<print-page data-raw-toggle>Print this page</print-page>{% endset %}
  <code-block language="html" label="Print button component">{{ _codePrint | escape }}</code-block>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Attribute</th>
        <th>Effect</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-raw-toggle</code></td>
        <td>Shows a checkbox labeled &ldquo;Print without VB styles&rdquo;</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-label</code></td>
        <td>Custom button label (default: element text content or &ldquo;Print this page&rdquo;)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>The component hides itself in print. Add <code>data-no-print</code> to the component for explicit documentation, though it is redundant.</p>
</section>


<!-- Opt-Out -->
<section id="opt-out">
  <h2>Opting Out</h2>
  <p>If you want the page to print exactly as it appears on screen &mdash; no token reset, no element hiding, no layout linearization &mdash; add <code>data-print-raw</code> to the <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> element.</p>

  {% set _codeRaw %}<html lang="en" data-print-raw>{% endset %}
  <code-block language="html" label="Disable VB print styles">{{ _codeRaw | escape }}</code-block>

  <p>This disables all VB print optimizations. The <code>@page</code> margin rules still apply (they cannot be scoped to a selector), but everything else is skipped.</p>

  <p>The <code>&lt;print-page data-raw-toggle&gt;</code> component provides this as a user-facing checkbox.</p>
</section>


